[HealthMap/ProMED map of Minnesota, United States: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=8695268,41983]

[A vaccine is available for horses. The WNV vaccine is often combined with eastern and western equine encephalitis, and tetanus. One vaccine to help prevent potentially deadly consequences for your horses is something every horse owner should be vaccinating with. Please consult your veterinarian regarding getting your horse vaccinated. Also please remember to use mosquito/fly spray approved for use on horses. Some components of sprays not specifically approved for horses can cause serious problems.

Please pay attention when a health department has a news release regarding mosquito trapping or birds with WNV or EEE. These are early warning signs to vaccinate your horses.

Remember to empty any standing water from old tires, potted plants, catch basins, or other locations that can hold even a small amount of water. These are perfect breeding grounds for mosquitoes. - Mod.TG]
